E–F), 
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1416807286" collectionCode="UMUT" country="Japan" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="331" location="University Museum" municipality="University" pageId="5" pageNumber="330" specimenCount="4" stateProvince="Tokyo" typeStatus="holotype">
<collectionCode box="[1178,1260,1960,1983]" country="Japan" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/kzwh-7f0x" name="University Museum, University of Tokyo" pageId="5" pageNumber="330">UMUT</collectionCode>
RA32555 (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1500,1522]" captionTargetBox="[196,1382,226,1420]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[151,1436,193,1478]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 12. Xestoleberis concava n. sp. Male holotype (UMUT RA 32550): (A) LV, (B) RV, (D 1 – D 4) normal sieve pores. Female paratype (UMUT RA 32555): (C) dorsal view. Female paratype (UMUT RA 32554): (E) top left hinge, bottom right hinge, (F) muscle scars. Scale bars: A – C, E – F = 100 µm; D 1 – D 4 = 5 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/257883/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="330">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
C). All 
<typeStatus box="[272,320,1996,2020]" pageId="5" pageNumber="330">type</typeStatus>
material was collected from the 
<typeStatus box="[712,760,1996,2020]" pageId="5" pageNumber="330">type</typeStatus>
