<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="331" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,2013]" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,332,357]" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">Etymology.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[340,440,332,355]" class="Ostracoda" family="Xestoleberididae" genus="Xestoleberis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="6" pageNumber="347" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="concava">
<emphasis box="[340,440,332,355]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">Concava</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
means arched or curved in Latin; the proximal structure of the hemipenes of this species is curved to form a concave, cupped structure.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="331" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,2013]" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,404,429]" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Carapace with widely rounded posterior and anterior ends; wider posterior than anterior. Anterior and ventral edges of valves lined with numerous simple marginal pores. Coloration in living specimens translucent brown. BO short segment with numerous fine terminating setae. Ejaculatory ducts arranged in S-shapes with inward exits. Furca reduced to two short setae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="331" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,2013]" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,548,573]" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">Description.</emphasis>
Carapace ovate, strongly inflated and vertically compressed (
<figureCitation box="[1064,1144,548,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1833,1855]" captionTargetBox="[163,1430,1079,1773]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[149,1434,1037,1799]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Xestoleberis becca n. sp. Male holotype (A) RV, (B) LV (UMUT RA 32562). Xestoleberis concava n. sp. Female paratype (C) RV, (D) LV (UMUT RA 32550). Xestoleberis gracilariaii n. sp. Male holotype (E) RV, (F) LV (UMUT RA 32531). Xestoleberis marcula n. sp. Male holotype (G) RV, (H) LV (UMUT RA 32556). Xestoleberis natuvuensis n. sp. Female paratype (I) RV, (J) LV (UMUT RA 32543). Xestoleberis penna n. sp. Female paratype (K) RV, (L) LV (UMUT RA 32538). Xestoleberis petrosa n. sp. Male holotype (M) RV, (N) LV (UMUT RA 32524). Scale bar: 200 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208332/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">Figs. 2</figureCitation>
A–B, 12A–F). Maximum valve length range: 524 µm–546 µm, maximum valve height range: 324 µm–335 µm (
<tableCitation box="[1110,1196,583,608]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="15.[151,235,152,174]" captionText="TABLE 2. Maximum lengths and heights of the type specimens for the seven new Fijian Xestoleberis species described in this paper." pageId="6" pageNumber="331">Table 2</tableCitation>
). Maximum height at mid-length. Dorsal margin convex, ventral margin slightly sinuous. Both anterior and posterior vestibula narrow; posterior narrower than anterior. Merodont hinge. Normal sieve pores scattered over carapace; those lining anterior and antero-ventral edges of carapace more recessed and some with smooth circumferences. Scar pattern: topmost scar of posterior row of four adductor scars U-shaped, single anterior scar V-shaped.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,2013]" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">
An1 with six podomeres; first two big, wide and rectangular, third to sixth small and quadrate (
<figureCitation box="[1291,1359,764,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1705,1727]" captionTargetBox="[173,1384,212,1665]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,193,1684]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Xestoleberis concava n. sp. Female paratype (UMUT RA 32552): (A) An 1, (A’) An 1 terminating setae, (B) An 2. (B’) An 2 claws, (C) Md coxa, (D) Md palp, (E) Md exopodite, (M) Furca. Male holotype (UMUT RA 32550): (F) Mx palp and endites, (F’) Mx palp, (G) Mx branchial plate, (H) BO, (I) L 5, (J) L 6, (K) L 7, (L) Hp. Scale bars: 50 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208334/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
A–A’). Second podomere with one medial seta, third podomere with one dorsal apical seta, fourth and fifth podomeres with one long and one fine dorsal apical setae. Terminating setae of sixth podomere: one stout with pointed tip, one slender and round tipped, one whip-like, and two fine. An2 with one ventral apical seta on first endopodite podomere (
<figureCitation box="[278,347,908,933]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1705,1727]" captionTargetBox="[173,1384,212,1665]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,193,1684]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Xestoleberis concava n. sp. Female paratype (UMUT RA 32552): (A) An 1, (A’) An 1 terminating setae, (B) An 2. (B’) An 2 claws, (C) Md coxa, (D) Md palp, (E) Md exopodite, (M) Furca. Male holotype (UMUT RA 32550): (F) Mx palp and endites, (F’) Mx palp, (G) Mx branchial plate, (H) BO, (I) L 5, (J) L 6, (K) L 7, (L) Hp. Scale bars: 50 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208334/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
B–B’). Two dorsal and ventral medial setae (longer ventral medial setae hirsute) and stout hirsute ventral apical seta on second endopodite podomere. Very fine serrations on one of two terminating claws. Md coxa with six pointed and two lobate teeth and one fine seta (
<figureCitation box="[777,844,980,1005]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1705,1727]" captionTargetBox="[173,1384,212,1665]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,193,1684]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Xestoleberis concava n. sp. Female paratype (UMUT RA 32552): (A) An 1, (A’) An 1 terminating setae, (B) An 2. (B’) An 2 claws, (C) Md coxa, (D) Md palp, (E) Md exopodite, (M) Furca. Male holotype (UMUT RA 32550): (F) Mx palp and endites, (F’) Mx palp, (G) Mx branchial plate, (H) BO, (I) L 5, (J) L 6, (K) L 7, (L) Hp. Scale bars: 50 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208334/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
C–E), palp with four podomeres: two medial setae at junction of first and second podomeres, and second and third podomeres, second podomere with one dorsal and two ventral apical setae, third podomere with five long dorsal and one stout ventral apical setae, fourth podomere with three stout terminating setae (two long and one short). Exopodite with at least two long setuled setae. 
<collectingCountry box="[1341,1380,1088,1111]" name="Mexico" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">Mx</collectingCountry>
with two segmented palp; first segment with three distal dorsal-apical setae and second podomere with one fine ventral medial seta and three terminating setae (two thick and one fine) (
<figureCitation box="[878,945,1159,1184]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1705,1727]" captionTargetBox="[173,1384,212,1665]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,193,1684]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Xestoleberis concava n. sp. Female paratype (UMUT RA 32552): (A) An 1, (A’) An 1 terminating setae, (B) An 2. (B’) An 2 claws, (C) Md coxa, (D) Md palp, (E) Md exopodite, (M) Furca. Male holotype (UMUT RA 32550): (F) Mx palp and endites, (F’) Mx palp, (G) Mx branchial plate, (H) BO, (I) L 5, (J) L 6, (K) L 7, (L) Hp. Scale bars: 50 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208334/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
F–G). Branchial plate with 16 setuled setae. BO is symmetrical; short segment with numerous fine terminating setae (
<figureCitation box="[971,1039,1196,1221]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1705,1727]" captionTargetBox="[173,1384,212,1665]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,193,1684]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Xestoleberis concava n. sp. Female paratype (UMUT RA 32552): (A) An 1, (A’) An 1 terminating setae, (B) An 2. (B’) An 2 claws, (C) Md coxa, (D) Md palp, (E) Md exopodite, (M) Furca. Male holotype (UMUT RA 32550): (F) Mx palp and endites, (F’) Mx palp, (G) Mx branchial plate, (H) BO, (I) L 5, (J) L 6, (K) L 7, (L) Hp. Scale bars: 50 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208334/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
H).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,2013]" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">
Basal setal formula for L5 1+1:2:1 and L6 and L7 1+1:1:1 (
<figureCitation box="[932,1005,1231,1256]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1705,1727]" captionTargetBox="[173,1384,212,1665]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,193,1684]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Xestoleberis concava n. sp. Female paratype (UMUT RA 32552): (A) An 1, (A’) An 1 terminating setae, (B) An 2. (B’) An 2 claws, (C) Md coxa, (D) Md palp, (E) Md exopodite, (M) Furca. Male holotype (UMUT RA 32550): (F) Mx palp and endites, (F’) Mx palp, (G) Mx branchial plate, (H) BO, (I) L 5, (J) L 6, (K) L 7, (L) Hp. Scale bars: 50 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208334/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">
Fig. 
<date box="[990,1005,1232,1256]" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">4</date>
</figureCitation>
I–K). Knee setae of all legs hirsute. Terminating claws L5 stout, short and curved, L6 smooth, stout, long and curved and L7 smooth, stout, and straight. Hp with asymmetrical, wide, rounded to sub-rounded distal processes; one has very rounded, U-shaped end, other with sub-rounded, almost quadrate end (
<figureCitation box="[717,783,1340,1365]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1705,1727]" captionTargetBox="[173,1384,212,1665]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,193,1684]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Xestoleberis concava n. sp. Female paratype (UMUT RA 32552): (A) An 1, (A’) An 1 terminating setae, (B) An 2. (B’) An 2 claws, (C) Md coxa, (D) Md palp, (E) Md exopodite, (M) Furca. Male holotype (UMUT RA 32550): (F) Mx palp and endites, (F’) Mx palp, (G) Mx branchial plate, (H) BO, (I) L 5, (J) L 6, (K) L 7, (L) Hp. Scale bars: 50 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208334/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
L). Proximal ends of capsules acutely angled and proximal support structure shaped like inverted T that forms cup-like structure. Furca two short fine setae on small rounded base.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="331" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,2013]" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,1447,1472]" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">Distribution.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[361,601,1448,1472]" class="Ostracoda" family="Xestoleberididae" genus="Xestoleberis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="6" pageNumber="331" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="concava" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[361,601,1448,1472]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">Xestoleberis concava</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[609,674,1447,1472]" pageId="6" pageNumber="331" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[609,674,1447,1472]" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">n. sp.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
specimens were collected from two locations, Naselesele, Taveuni 
<collectingCountry box="[151,219,1484,1509]" name="Iceland" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">Island</collectingCountry>
(
<typeStatus box="[237,287,1484,1508]" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">type</typeStatus>
locality) and the fine sand gently sloping beach coast of Viani Village in Natewa Bay, Vanua Levu 
<collectingCountry box="[151,219,1519,1544]" name="Iceland" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">Island</collectingCountry>
(P5, 
<figureCitation box="[289,359,1519,1544]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1304,1326]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,267,1272]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,267,1282]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. P 1 – P 6: present study specimen collection sites. B 1 – B 3: collection sites for Xestoleberis variegata and Xestoleberis curta by Brady (1890). Refer to Table 1 for site details. Color-coded circles indicating the geographical distribution of Fijian Xestoleberis species (seven new species described by the present paper and two species reported by Brady (1890 )). Ocean depth contours and the fast flowing Bligh Water currents are also illustrated." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208331/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
, Table 1). In addition to the 
<typeStatus box="[712,810,1519,1544]" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">holotype</typeStatus>
habitat (
<taxonomicName box="[919,1126,1520,1544]" class="Ulvophyceae" family="Halimedaceae" genus="Halimeda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Bryopsidales" pageId="6" pageNumber="331" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="species" species="opuntia">
<emphasis box="[919,1126,1520,1544]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">Halimeda opuntia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), prominent counts of the specimens were also obtained from a short red alga (
<taxonomicName box="[790,949,1556,1580]" class="Florideophyceae" family="Pterocladiaceae" genus="Pterocladiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Nemaliales" pageId="6" pageNumber="331" phylum="Rhodophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[790,949,1556,1580]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">Pterocladiella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp.) and a green filamentous alga (
<taxonomicName class="Ulvophyceae" family="Ulvaceae" genus="Ulva" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" order="Ulvales" pageId="6" pageNumber="331" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="species" species="intestinalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">Ulva intestinalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="331" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,2013]" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1628,1653]" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[324,565,1628,1652]" class="Ostracoda" family="Xestoleberididae" genus="Xestoleberis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="6" pageNumber="331" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="concava" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[324,565,1628,1652]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">Xestoleberis concava</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[575,641,1628,1653]" pageId="6" pageNumber="331" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[575,641,1628,1653]" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">n. sp.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Titterton &amp; Whatley, 2005" authorityName="Titterton &amp; Whatley" authorityYear="2005" box="[797,1436,1628,1653]" class="Ostracoda" family="Xestoleberididae" genus="Xestoleberis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="6" pageNumber="331" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="posterotruncata">
<emphasis box="[797,1123,1628,1652]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">Xestoleberis posterotruncata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Titterton" box="[1132,1436,1628,1653]" pageId="6" pageNumber="331" refString="Titterton, R. &amp; Whatley, R. (2005) Recent marine ostracoda from the Solomon Islands. Part 2: Cytheracea, Xestoleberididae. Revista Espanola de Micropaleontologia, 37 (2), 291 - 313." type="journal article" year="2005">Titterton &amp; Whatley, 2005</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[159,232,1663,1688]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1705,1727]" captionTargetBox="[173,1384,212,1665]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,193,1684]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Xestoleberis concava n. sp. Female paratype (UMUT RA 32552): (A) An 1, (A’) An 1 terminating setae, (B) An 2. (B’) An 2 claws, (C) Md coxa, (D) Md palp, (E) Md exopodite, (M) Furca. Male holotype (UMUT RA 32550): (F) Mx palp and endites, (F’) Mx palp, (G) Mx branchial plate, (H) BO, (I) L 5, (J) L 6, (K) L 7, (L) Hp. Scale bars: 50 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208334/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
, No. 27, Pl. 4, 
<figureCitation box="[421,532,1663,1688]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 1" captionStart-1="FIGURE 2" captionStart-2="FIGURE 3" captionStart-3="FIGURE 4" captionStart-4="FIGURE 5" captionStartId-0="1.[151,250,1304,1326]" captionStartId-1="4.[151,250,1833,1855]" captionStartId-2="5.[151,250,1699,1721]" captionStartId-3="7.[151,250,1705,1727]" captionStartId-4="8.[151,250,1858,1880]" captionTargetBox-0="[151,1436,267,1272]" captionTargetBox-1="[163,1430,1079,1773]" captionTargetBox-2="[189,1391,233,1640]" captionTargetBox-3="[173,1384,212,1665]" captionTargetBox-4="[182,1401,429,1803]" captionTargetId-0="figure@1.[151,1436,267,1282]" captionTargetId-1="figure@4.[149,1434,1037,1799]" captionTargetId-2="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1678]" captionTargetId-3="figure@7.[151,1436,193,1684]" captionTargetId-4="figure@8.[151,1436,409,1837]" captionTargetPageId-0="1" captionTargetPageId-1="4" captionTargetPageId-2="5" captionTargetPageId-3="7" captionTargetPageId-4="8" captionText-0="FIGURE 1. P 1 – P 6: present study specimen collection sites. B 1 – B 3: collection sites for Xestoleberis variegata and Xestoleberis curta by Brady (1890). Refer to Table 1 for site details. Color-coded circles indicating the geographical distribution of Fijian Xestoleberis species (seven new species described by the present paper and two species reported by Brady (1890 )). Ocean depth contours and the fast flowing Bligh Water currents are also illustrated." captionText-1="FIGURE 2. Xestoleberis becca n. sp. Male holotype (A) RV, (B) LV (UMUT RA 32562). Xestoleberis concava n. sp. Female paratype (C) RV, (D) LV (UMUT RA 32550). Xestoleberis gracilariaii n. sp. Male holotype (E) RV, (F) LV (UMUT RA 32531). Xestoleberis marcula n. sp. Male holotype (G) RV, (H) LV (UMUT RA 32556). Xestoleberis natuvuensis n. sp. Female paratype (I) RV, (J) LV (UMUT RA 32543). Xestoleberis penna n. sp. Female paratype (K) RV, (L) LV (UMUT RA 32538). Xestoleberis petrosa n. sp. Male holotype (M) RV, (N) LV (UMUT RA 32524). Scale bar: 200 µm." captionText-2="FIGURE 3. Xestoleberis becca. n. sp. Male holotype (UMUT RA 32562): (A) An 1, (A’) terminating An 1 setae, (B) An 2, (B’) An 2 claws, (F) Mx, (F’) Mx palp, (G) BO. (H) L 5, (I) L 6, (J) L 7, (K) Hp. Female paratype (UMUT RA 32564): (C) Md coxa, (D) Md palp, (E) Md exopodite, (L) Furca. Scale bars: 50 µm." captionText-3="FIGURE 4. Xestoleberis concava n. sp. Female paratype (UMUT RA 32552): (A) An 1, (A’) An 1 terminating setae, (B) An 2. (B’) An 2 claws, (C) Md coxa, (D) Md palp, (E) Md exopodite, (M) Furca. Male holotype (UMUT RA 32550): (F) Mx palp and endites, (F’) Mx palp, (G) Mx branchial plate, (H) BO, (I) L 5, (J) L 6, (K) L 7, (L) Hp. Scale bars: 50 µm." captionText-4="FIGURE 5. Xestoleberis gracilariaii n. sp. Female paratype (UMUT RA 32533): (A) An 1, (A’) An 1 terminating setae, (B) An 2, (B’) An 2 claws, (C) Md coxa, (D) Md palp, (E) Md exopodite, (F) Mx palp and endites, (F’) Mx palp, (G) Mx branchial plate, (I) L 5, (J) L 6, (K) L 7. Male holotype (UMUT RA 32531): (H) BO, (L) Hp. Female paratype (UMUT RA 32534): (M) Furca. Scale bars: 50 µm." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/208331/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/208332/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/208333/files/figure.png" httpUri-3="https://zenodo.org/record/208334/files/figure.png" httpUri-4="https://zenodo.org/record/208335/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">Figs. 1–5</figureCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Titterton" box="[548,854,1663,1688]" pageId="6" pageNumber="331" refString="Titterton, R. &amp; Whatley, R. (2005) Recent marine ostracoda from the Solomon Islands. Part 2: Cytheracea, Xestoleberididae. Revista Espanola de Micropaleontologia, 37 (2), 291 - 313." type="journal article" year="2005">Titterton &amp; Whatley 2005</bibRefCitation>
) reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[1043,1234,1663,1688]" name="Solomon Islands" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">Solomon Islands</collectingCountry>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Hartmann-Schroder, 1978" authorityName="Hartmann-Schroder" authorityYear="1978" class="Ostracoda" family="Xestoleberididae" genus="Xestoleberis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="6" pageNumber="331" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cauticola">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">Xestoleberis cauticola</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hartmann-Schroder" box="[266,561,1700,1725]" pageId="6" pageNumber="331" refString="Hartmann-Schroder, G. (1978) Zur Kenntnis des Eulitorals der australischen Kusten unter besonderer Berucksichtigung der Polychaeten und Ostracoden. Mitteilungen aus dem Hamburgischen Zoologischen Museum und Institut, 75, 63 - 219." type="journal article" year="1978">Hartmann-Schröder, 1978</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(Abb. 370–384, Tafel XII 
<figureCitation box="[880,1018,1700,1725]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 12" captionStart-1="FIGURE 13" captionStartId-0="20.[151,250,1500,1522]" captionStartId-1="21.[151,250,1848,1870]" captionTargetBox-0="[196,1382,226,1420]" captionTargetBox-1="[163,1420,313,1821]" captionTargetId-0="figure@20.[151,1436,193,1478]" captionTargetId-1="figure@21.[151,1436,285,1827]" captionTargetPageId-0="20" captionTargetPageId-1="21" captionText-0="FIGURE 12. Xestoleberis concava n. sp. Male holotype (UMUT RA 32550): (A) LV, (B) RV, (D 1 – D 4) normal sieve pores. Female paratype (UMUT RA 32555): (C) dorsal view. Female paratype (UMUT RA 32554): (E) top left hinge, bottom right hinge, (F) muscle scars. Scale bars: A – C, E – F = 100 µm; D 1 – D 4 = 5 µm." captionText-1="FIGURE 13. Xestoleberis petrosa. n. sp. Male paratype (UMUT RA 32528): (A) LV, (B) RV, (F 1) normal sieve pore, (F 2) normal simple pore. Female paratype (UMUT RA 32530): (C) dorsal view. Female paratype (UMUT RA 32529): (D) top left hinge, bottom right hinge, (E) muscle scars. Xestoleberis gracilariaii n. sp. Male paratype (UMUT RA 32535): (G) LV, (J 1) Male normal simple pore, (J 2 – J 3) male normal sieve pores. Female paratype (UMUT RA 32537): (H) dorsal view. Female paratype (UMUT RA 32536): (I) top right hinge, bottom left hinge. Scale bars: A – D, G – H = 100 µm; E, I = 50 µm; F 1 – F 2, J 1 – J 3 = 5 µm." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/257883/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/257884/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">Figs. 12–13</figureCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hartmann-Schroder" box="[1034,1324,1700,1725]" pageId="6" pageNumber="331" refString="Hartmann-Schroder, G. (1978) Zur Kenntnis des Eulitorals der australischen Kusten unter besonderer Berucksichtigung der Polychaeten und Ostracoden. Mitteilungen aus dem Hamburgischen Zoologischen Museum und Institut, 75, 63 - 219." type="journal article" year="1978">Hartmann-Schröder 1978</bibRefCitation>
) reported from northwestern 
<collectingCountry box="[377,483,1735,1760]" name="Australia" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">Australia</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[500,829,1736,1760]" class="Ostracoda" family="Xestoleberididae" genus="Xestoleberis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="6" pageNumber="331" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="posterotruncata">
<emphasis box="[500,829,1736,1760]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">Xestoleberis posterotruncata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has both simple and branching pore canals in the anterior marginal zone, while 
<taxonomicName box="[485,609,1773,1796]" class="Ostracoda" family="Xestoleberididae" genus="Xestoleberis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="6" pageNumber="331" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="concava" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[485,609,1773,1796]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">X. concava</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[616,678,1772,1797]" pageId="6" pageNumber="331" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[616,678,1772,1797]" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">n. sp.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
only has simple anterior marginal pores. The L7 of 
<taxonomicName box="[1257,1391,1772,1796]" class="Ostracoda" family="Xestoleberididae" genus="Xestoleberis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="6" pageNumber="331" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cauticola">
<emphasis box="[1257,1391,1772,1796]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">X. cauticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a very thin and straight terminating claw tapering to a sharp point and with a mass of short, fine setae at the base of the claw. The L7 claw of 
<taxonomicName box="[438,677,1844,1868]" class="Ostracoda" family="Xestoleberididae" genus="Xestoleberis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="6" pageNumber="331" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="concava" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[438,677,1844,1868]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">Xestoleberis concava</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[684,747,1844,1869]" pageId="6" pageNumber="331" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[684,747,1844,1869]" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">n. sp.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
tapers to a point with a slight curve. 
<taxonomicName box="[1167,1406,1844,1868]" class="Ostracoda" family="Xestoleberididae" genus="Xestoleberis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="6" pageNumber="331" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="concava" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[1167,1406,1844,1868]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">Xestoleberis concava</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="6" pageNumber="331" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[251,392,1880,1904]" class="Ostracoda" family="Xestoleberididae" genus="Xestoleberis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="6" pageNumber="331" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cauticola">
<emphasis box="[251,392,1880,1904]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">X. cauticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
ejaculatory duct S-shaped arrangements varies, Hp distal processes of 
<taxonomicName box="[1247,1389,1880,1904]" class="Ostracoda" family="Xestoleberididae" genus="Xestoleberis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="6" pageNumber="331" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cauticola">
<emphasis box="[1247,1389,1880,1904]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">X. cauticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are triangular with narrow, rounded tips, while those of 
<taxonomicName box="[738,862,1917,1940]" class="Ostracoda" family="Xestoleberididae" genus="Xestoleberis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="6" pageNumber="331" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="concava" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[738,862,1917,1940]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">X. concava</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[870,933,1916,1941]" pageId="6" pageNumber="331" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[870,933,1916,1941]" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">n. sp.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
are sub-triangular with widely rounded tips. 
<taxonomicName box="[151,400,1952,1976]" class="Ostracoda" family="Xestoleberididae" genus="Xestoleberis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="6" pageNumber="331" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cauticola">
<emphasis box="[151,400,1952,1976]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">Xestoleberis cauticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has sub-rounded proximal capsule ends in contrast with the acutely angled proximal capsule ends of 
<taxonomicName box="[239,363,1989,2012]" class="Ostracoda" family="Xestoleberididae" genus="Xestoleberis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="6" pageNumber="331" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="concava" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[239,363,1989,2012]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">X. concava</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[371,434,1988,2013]" pageId="6" pageNumber="331" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[371,434,1988,2013]" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">n. sp.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
